<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2016-11-12</DATELINE><TITLE>Pharmacological Management and Prevention Of Exacerbations of Chronic Obstructive Pulmonary Disease in Hospitalized Patients</TITLE><BODY>Rapid-acting bronchodilators, systemic corticosteroids, and antibiotics are among the keys to managing exacerbations of chronic obstructive pulmonary disease. Preventing exacerbations should also be a component of therapy for the disease.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>